a + b\sqrt{2} = x + y\sqrt{2}\\ \implies a-x = (y-b)\sqrt{2}\\ \implies (a-x)^2 = 2(y-b)^2\\ \overset{y - b \neq 0}{\implies} 2 = \left(\frac{a-x}{y-b}\right)^{\!2}.
